{{Infobox company | name = Apprehensive Films | logo = [[Image:Apprehensive Films.jpg|Apprehensive Films logo]] | type = | foundation = [[1997 in film|1997]]<ref name="About The GrindHouse"/> | location = [[Citrus Heights, California]], [[United States]]<ref name="Contact Apprehensive Films">{{cite web |url=http://www.afcinema.net/contact.html |title=Contact Apprehensive Films |author= |date= |work= |publisher=Apprehensive Films |accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref> | key_people = | num_employees = | parent = | industry = [[Film]]s | products = | revenue = | operating profit = | homepage = http://www.afcinema.net/ }}
'''Apprehensive Films''' is an independent American [[film]] [[production company|production]] and [[film distributor|distribution]] company. Established in [[1997 in film|1997]] as a production company, Apprehensive Films' main focus was low-budget [[Grindhouse]]-inspired films shot in [[Super 8 mm film]] and [[16 mm film]].<ref name="About The GrindHouse">{{cite web |url=http://www.thecrippledmasters.com/newafaboutus.html |title=About The GrindHouse |author= |date= |work= |publisher=TheGrindHouse.net |accessdate=20 July 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100619144815/http://www.thecrippledmasters.com/newafaboutus.html| archivedate= 19 June 2010 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> In [[2006 in film|2006]], Apprehensive Films became a DVD distributor specializing in [[cult film|cult]], [[horror film|horror]] and [[exploitation film]].<ref name="About The GrindHouse"/> In [[2009 in film|2009]], Apprehensive Films took over the television distribution of the [[horror host]]ed television series ''[[Cinema Insomnia]]'' which led to their re-licensing the show to [[AMGTV]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.lastdoorwayproductions.com/news_mr_lobo.html |title= "CINEMA INSOMNIA" AND AMGTV ARE BRINGING HOSTED "MIDNIGHT MOVIES" TO PRIME TIME AND COAST TO COAST!}}</ref>
