''Drogas Wave'' received generally favorable reviews from critics. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[standard score|normalized]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream publications, the album received an [[weighted arithmetic mean|average]] score of 73, based on 5 reviews.{{sfn|Metacritic|2018}}

==Commercial performance==
''Drogas Wave'' debuted at number 60 on the US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], with first-week sales of 4,951 copies in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Eustice|first1=Kyle|title=Hip Hop Album Sales: Brockhampton Nabs Billboard 200's Coveted Spot With "Iridescence"|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.48648/title.hip-hop-album-sales-brockhampton-nabs-billboard-200s-coveted-spot-with-iridescence|date=October 1, 2018|accessdate=October 3, 2018}}</ref>

