{{Unreferenced|date=April 2008}} {{Infobox album | name = How You Luv That Vol. 2 | type = studio | artist = [[Big Tymers]] | cover = Sddefault.png | alt = | released = September 22, 1998 | recorded = February – August 1998 | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Southern Hip Hop]] | length = | label = {{hlist|[[Cash Money Records|Cash Money]]|[[Universal Records (defunct record label)|Universal]]}} | producer = [[Mannie Fresh]], [[Birdman (rapper)]] <small>(Executive Producer), Ronald "Slim" Williams <small>(Executive Producer) | prev_title = [[How You Luv That]] | prev_year = 1998 | next_title = [[I Got That Work]] | next_year = 2000 | misc = {{Singles | name = How You Luv That Vol. 2 | type = studio | single1 = "Big Ballin" | single1date = 1998 | single2 = "Stun'N (Remix)" | single2date = 1998 }} }} {{Album ratings | rev1 = [[Allmusic]] | rev1Score = {{Rating|2.5|5|score=2.4 stars on a 5 point scale}} [{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r372497|pure_url=yes}} link] | rev2 = ''[[The Source (magazine)|The Source]]'' | rev2Score = {{Rating|3|5}} [http://www.cduniverse.com/productinfo.asp?pid=1202630&style=music link] | noprose = yes }}
'''''How You Luv That Vol. 2''''' is the second album by rap duo [[Big Tymers]] released in later 1998. The singles are "Big Ballin'" and "Stun'n (Remix)". Mannie Fresh produced the album. The album featured guests [[Bun B]], [[Lil Wayne]], Cadillac, [[Juvenile (rapper)|Juvenile]], [[Papa Reu|Paparue]] & [[B.G. (rapper)|B.G.]] The upper middle of the cover shows [[B.G. (rapper)]] in pre-planned early artwork for his album, ''[[Chopper City In The Ghetto]]'', which was released a year later.
