'''Sky Cable''' (stylized as '''SKY cable''') is a cable television service of [[Sky (cable company)|Sky Cable Corporation]].<ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/bbcworldwide/worldwidestories/pressreleases/2011/01_january/cbeebies_philippines. shtml {{Dead link |date=April 2017}}</ref> Its franchise area covers [[Metro Manila]], and its suburb or neighboring areas and it is also in provincial areas that both digital and few analog services, and it has 700,000 subscribers controlling 45% of the cable TV market.<ref>http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/business/06/28/12/skycable-focus-digitization-efforts-allots-p1-b-capex</ref>

== History ==
{{prose|date=August 2012}}

Since it started community antenna television system operation in the Philippines on January 26, 1992, SkyCable provides cable Internet, VoIP services and digital cable TV service.

