* On June 6, 1990, SkyCable Corporation was incorporated via 79.3% stake in Sky Vision Corporation, operator of cable brands, SkyCable and Sun Cable.<ref name="pse.com. ph">http://www.pse.com.ph/html/ListedCompanies/pdf/2010/ABS_17A_Apr2010.pdf {{Dead link |date=April 2017}}</ref>
* On April 18, 1991, Sky Vision Corporation was incorporated and ventures into cable television (SkyCable and Sun Cable), communication, system, television media, shopping network (Sky Mall) and film distribution (Sky Jemah). It is owned 18.8% by ABS-CBN Corporation and 78% by Lopez Inc.<ref name="pse.com. ph"/>
* On March 30, 1995, Central CATV Inc. was granted a 28-year provisional franchise to establish, construct, maintain and operated community antenna television system in the Philippines through Republic Act 7969.<ref>[http://www.chanrobles.com/republicacts/republicactno7969.html Philippine Laws, Statutes And Codes - Chan Robles Virtual Law Library<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
* In 1997, Sky Vision Corporation acquired 47% of Pilipino Cable Corp., operator of Sun Cable for P900 million.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120910193956/http://www.philstar.com/Article.aspx?articleid=67845 Sky Vision buys Lorenzo stake in Pilipino Cable - The Philippine Star » News » Business<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
* In 1997, SkyCable launches its first cable TV branded credit card in the Philippines, the SkyCard MasterCard with SolidBank and the SkyCard-Citibank MasterCard with [[Citibank Philippines|Citibank N. A.]]<ref name="lopez-holdings. ph">[http://www.lopez-holdings.ph/news.php?id=108 Lopez Holdings Corporation<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809143656/http://www.lopez-holdings.ph/news.php?id=108 |date=2011-08-09 }}</ref>
* In 2001, Benpress Holdings Inc. and [[Philippine Long Distance Telephone Company]] signed a master consolidation agreement for SkyCable Corporation to consolidate its interest.<ref>[http://www.lopez-holdings.ph/portfolio.php?id=40 Lopez Holdings Corporation<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
* In July 2001, Unilink Communications Corp. operator of Home Cable, Philippines second largest cable TV company, merged its CATV operation to SkyCable and created Beyond Cable Inc. with an [[enterprise value]] of P14.5 billion. Beyond Cable Inc. controls 66.5% through Benpress Holdings Corp. and 33.5% through [[MediaQuest Holdings, Inc.]]<ref>[https://archive.is/20120907131317/http://www.philstar.com/Article.aspx?articleId=96588 Home, SkyCable merge - The Philippine Star » News » Business<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://cerphin.net/balita/GMA-Network-opposes-SkyCableHome-Cable-full-consolidation/artikulo/46977/ GMA Network opposes SkyCable-Home Cable full consolidation<!-- Bot generated title -->]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723040801/http://cerphin.net/balita/GMA-Network-opposes-SkyCableHome-Cable-full-consolidation/artikulo/46977/ |date=2011-07-23 }}</ref>
* On December 7, 2001, Beyond Cable Holdings Inc. was incorporated.<ref name="pse.com. ph"/>
* In April 2008, then ABS-CBN Broadcasting Corporation (now [[ABS-CBN Corporation]]), which owns about two-thirds of the equity of SkyCable, started consolidating the cable company’s fiscal result into its financial report including SkyCable’s general and administrative expenses or the GAEX.<ref>http://ir.abs-cbn.com/ir/shareholderfaqs.aspx</ref>
* In May 2011, Singaporean firm [[STT Communications|Sampaquita Communications Pte. Ltd.]] acquired 40 percent of SkyCable through Philippine Depositary Receipts worth P3.612 billion and P250 million of convertible notes to fund the expansion of SkyCable’s broadband Internet and cable TV services.<ref>[http://business.inquirer.net/money/topstories/view/20110512-336178/Singaporean-firm-gets-40-of-SkyCable Business - Singaporean firm gets 40% of SkyCable - INQUIRER. net<!-- Bot generated title -->]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120325114855/http://business.inquirer.net/money/topstories/view/20110512-336178/Singaporean-firm-gets-40-of-SkyCable |date=2012-03-25 }}</ref>
* On May 11, 2012, SkyCable bought Destiny Cable Inc., Uni-Cable TV Inc. and Solid Broadband Corp.'s cable TV and broadband internet assets and subscribers with consolidating value of P3.497 billion.<ref>http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/business/05/11/12/sky-cable-buys-destiny-cable’s-assets</ref><ref>http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/business/05/14/12/skycable-aims-grow-market-signs-3-deals</ref>

== Basic cable packages ==

In order to be competitive in the cable TV industry, SkyCable adopts an alternative pricing model for its subscribers. It allows its subscribers to select their own packages or channels, comparable to a pay per channel service most generally used in the United States. SkyCable also introduces the package-pricing model typically used by other cable television providers in which channels are classified into packages.

=== Postpaid ===

The SkyCable postpaid bundles are categorized into 10 clusters named as Select, Bronze 299, Bronze 399, Bronze 499, Silver HD, Gold HD, Postpaid HD (299, 549, 999, 1999) and a separate payment scheme for its Premium/Pay-Per-View.<ref name="skycable. com">[http://www.skycable.com/mm_post_packages.aspx?id=11&pkg=HD&pg=Description&subid=1&cid=40 MM Postpaid Packages - SkyCable - Philippines' best cable service<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120914030725/http://www.skycable.com/mm_post_packages.aspx?id=11&pkg=HD&pg=Description&subid=1&cid=40 |date=2012-09-14 }}</ref>

* Select:  It is a customizable plan that allows its subscribers to choose channels on top of their preset package. Select plan is available on existing subscription either from Bronze 299, 399 and 499, Silver HD, Gold HD or Postpaid HD (299, 549, 999 and 1999) plans and also requires a digital set-top boxes.<ref>[http://www.skycable.com/mm_post_packages.aspx?id=9&pkg=Select&pg=Description&subid=1&cid=41 MM Postpaid Packages - SkyCable - Philippines' best cable service<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120914084144/http://www.skycable.com/mm_post_packages.aspx?id=9&pkg=Select&pg=Description&subid=1&cid=41 |date=2012-09-14 }}</ref>
* Bronze 299 (formerly 280): SkyCable Bronze 299 package consists of 20 basic channels.<ref>[http://www.skycable.com/mm_post_packages.aspx?id=14&pkg=280&pg=Description&subid=1&cid=42 MM Postpaid Packages - SkyCable - Philippines' best cable service<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120912041900/http://www.skycable.com/mm_post_packages.aspx?id=14&pkg=280&pg=Description&subid=1&cid=42 |date=2012-09-12 }}</ref> But as of October 1, 2015, it no longer offered for new subscribers for Greater Manila Area (NCR - inc. CAMANAVA and Rizal), Cavite, Laguna, San Jose del Monte, Bulacan and Bacolod and status of current subscribers remained unchanged for said mentioned areas. However, it continues offered for new subscribers in the rest of remaining provincial areas (Cebu, Davao, Baguio, Iloilo, Gen. Santos and Dumaguete).
* Plus:  SkyCable Plus package consists of 50 channels.<ref>[http://www.skycable.com/packages.aspx?id=13&pkg=Plus&pg=Description&subid=1&cid=43 Packages - SkyCable - Philippines' best cable service<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091207115610/http://www.skycable.com/packages.aspx?id=13&pkg=Plus&pg=Description&subid=1&cid=43 |date=2009-12-07 }}</ref> No longer offered to new subscribers; status of current subscribers uncertain.
* Bronze 399: SkyCable Bronze 399 consists of more or less than 30 channels. Available only in most of regional areas with digital service. Recently, as of November 2014, the plan (or package) were currently expanded its service in Metro Manila and areas nearby.<ref>[http://www.mysky.com.ph/baguio/skycable/plans.php ''SKY''cable basic plans for Baguio]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140708215939/http://www.mysky.com.ph/baguio/skycable/plans.php |date=2014-07-08 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.mysky.com.ph/bacolod/skycable/plans.php ''SKY''Cable basic plans for Bacolod]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140708074449/http://www.mysky.com.ph/bacolod/skycable/plans.php |date=2014-07-08 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.mysky.com.ph/iloilo/skycable/plans.php''SKY''cable basic plans for Iloilo]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810204808/http://www.mysky.com.ph/iloilo/skycable/plans.php |date=2014-08-10 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.mysky.com.ph/cebu/skycable/plans.php ''SKY''Cable basic plans for Cebu]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140709082236/http://www.mysky.com.ph/cebu/skycable/plans.php |date=2014-07-09 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.mysky.com.ph/davao/skycable/plans.php ''SKY''cable basic plans for Davao]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140709195804/http://www.mysky.com.ph/davao/skycable/plans.php |date=2014-07-09 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.mysky.com.ph/dumaguete/skycable/plans.php ''SKY''cable basic plans for Dumaguete]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140708050956/http://www.mysky.com.ph/dumaguete/skycable/plans.php |date=2014-07-08 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.mysky.com.ph/gensan/skycable/plans.php ''SKY''cable basic plans for GenSan]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140708100446/http://www.mysky.com.ph/gensan/skycable/plans.php |date=2014-07-08 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mysky.com.ph/manila/skycable/plans.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-11-27 |deadurl=yes |archi