{{Infobox book |name = The Oxford Book of English Madrigals |image = File:Oxford Book of English Madrigals.jpg |editor = [[Philip Ledger]] |cover_artist = [[The Five Senses (series)|Jan Brueghel the Elder & Peter Paul Rubens]] |country = United Kingdom |language = English |series = |subject = [[Sheet Music]] - Folk & Traditional |publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] |release_date = 1978 |media_type = Print ([[paperback]]) |pages = 403 |isbn = 978-0-19-343664-0 |website = [https://global.oup.com/academic/product/the-oxford-book-of-english-madrigals-9780193436640?cc=gb&lang=en& OUP.com] }}
'''''The Oxford Book of English Madrigals''''' was edited by [[Philip Ledger]], and published in 1978 by the [[Oxford University Press]]. It contains words and full music for some 60 of the [[madrigal (music)|madrigal]]s and songs of the [[English Madrigal School]].
When selecting works for this book, Ledger decided to represent the major composers of [[Early music of the British Isles|16th-century English music]] such as [[William Byrd]] and [[Thomas Morley]] with several madrigals, alongside individual works by lesser-known composers. Ledger collaborated with Andrew Parker, a [[musicology|musicologist]] from [[King's College, Cambridge]], who researched texts to the songs and supplemented the collection with annotations and critical commentary.<ref name="milsom">{{cite journal|last1=Milsom|first1=John|title=Music|journal=Early Music|date=1 October 1983|volume=11|issue=4|pages=545–547|doi=10.1093/earlyj/11.4.545|url=http://em.oxfordjournals.org/content/11/4/545.extract|accessdate=30 September 2016|language=en|issn=0306-1078|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160930133540/http://em.oxfordjournals.org/content/11/4/545.extract|archivedate=30 September 2016|deadurl=no}}</ref>
In 1978, the choral group [[Pro Cantione Antiqua]] released a recording, directed by Ledger, of selected songs from this book.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Henry|first1=Derrick|title=The Listener's Guide to Medieval and Renaissance Music.|date=1983|publisher=Facts on File|location=New York, N.Y.|isbn=9780871967510|page=132|edition=1. Aufl.}}</ref>
==Contents== The collection contains the following madrigals:
